# Dev tooling

## Scripts (`package.json`)

| Script | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `yarn ci` | `rm -rf node_modules` then frozen install; `postinstall` runs `yarn start` |
| `yarn start` | `npx gulp` — Browser-Sync on `./`, default port 3000 |
| `yarn verify` | `yarn install --check-files` |

## Gulp (`gulpfile.js`)

Single default task: init Browser-Sync, watch `*.html` and `less/*.less`, reload on change.

Do not add heavy tooling (webpack, vite) unless the user requests a migration.

## VS Code / Cursor

- **Run and Debug**: "Open nalam.me (Browser-Sync)" starts the dev server then opens Chrome
- **Task**: `dev: Browser-Sync` for server only

## Dependencies

Dev only: `gulp`, `browser-sync`. No runtime npm dependencies for production (static site).
